Mark Oberholzer (centre) has been missing since Monday Picture: Supplied Kabega Park police have called for any information relating to the disappearance of Mark Oberholzer, 35, of Woodlands. While details surrounding the incident are still sketchy, police spokesman Warrant Officer Alwin Labans said Oberholzer was reported missing by friends on Monday. Labans said: We cannot say what clothing he had on at the time of his disappearance. His friends say he has a beard. Labans said police had no indication as to his whereabouts, and any information could be reported to Kabega Park police station. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share